Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.73,0:01:35.99,Title Part 5,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(402,394)\pos(107,923)\fs60}Episodio 21  The Mystery of King Crimson
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:33.53,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ugh, Narancia!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.53,0:01:36.74,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,{\an8}Are you seriously trying to eat \Nall the chocolates behind our backs?!{This is a stupid question. You literally answered it in the same sentence. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.74,0:01:38.03,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Give 'em back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.03,0:01:41.45,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I spent my own money on them, \Nso give 'em back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.45,0:01:44.54,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,There's only three left!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.33,0:01:42.83,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,{\an8}Narancia, I swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.83,0:01:44.29,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,{\an8}Selfish bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.29,0:01:46.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,{\an8}We're all hungry and want some, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.08,0:01:50.34,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The ladybug brooch is moving from the top of the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.34,0:01:51.09,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.59,0:01:54.88,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's headed down to the charnel house\N to try to cross through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.22,0:01:59.22,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati must have planted the brooch somewhere on the boss's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.22,0:02:02.89,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Giorno, if you don't mind, \Ncould you grab me a water?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:04.77,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I'm thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:07.94,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Also, watch what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.94,0:02:12.23,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We were ordered not to set foot on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.23,0:02:14.48,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You should stay on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:15.69,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:20.82,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Huh? Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:23.41,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,D-Did you eat them, Mista?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.41,0:02:26.12,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Cough 'em up, asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:29.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What the hell did you get on your cheek?{He literally says "AROUND your mouth", so he's referring to the smudge on Narancia's cheek. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.17,0:02:29.96,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.38,0:02:31.08,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.42,0:02:33.67,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Don't "Ah" me, you jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:35.67,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}S-So sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:37.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,When did you even stuff them in your mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.22,0:02:41.43,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, \Ndid I thank you yet, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:44.39,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,For getting the water for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:56.32,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This situation... is bizarre...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:06.54,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm unsure what it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.70,0:03:09.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...but something feels off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:11.58,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Hey, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.58,0:03:14.92,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Was your head up your ass when the boss told us not to set foot on the is{\fscx300}-{\r}{Behold, the inconsistent formatting between this line and the next! Not sure what would be the best way to do it tho. -Starfish}{Actually, this makes sense to me. Presumably in erased time he finished the sentence, but he says the rest after the jump since that time was lost, so it's technically separate from this sentence. -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:16.67,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...land?
Comment: 0,0:03:17.01,0:03:17.96,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:20.88,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This isn't normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.88,0:03:23.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Something strange is afoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.64,0:03:25.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This is bad! Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:27.85,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Where the hell are you going, Giorno?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.85,0:03:28.98,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.98,0:03:29.93,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.48,0:03:33.31,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes, I know he's on the move. {Line 46-53 copied from Episode 20v2 -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:36.90,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I know exactly where the brooch\Nyou put on the boss's body is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.90,0:03:39.94,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Right now, he's at the bottom of the stairs\N leading to the charnel house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:42.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He's right near the pillar that's \Nabout two meters away from the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:45.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But wait, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:48.04,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Something tells me... you're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:54.29,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati, your mission to escort Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:57.05,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...has come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:07.47,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Y-You conniving...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:10.23,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,For him to purposely try to restrain my arm...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.23,0:04:11.94,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:14.81,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But... King Crimson...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:15.73,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...has already...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:32.33,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:33.92,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I know where you're moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:36.75,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I can see your every move toward the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:42.17,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Within the domain of King Crimson's ability, all time is erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:47.89,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Not a single human besides myself can recall \Nwhere and how they moved within this time. {Not really true since Diavolo can recall it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.81,0:04:51.98,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Even the clouds in the sky remain \Nunaware that they've broken apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.98,0:04:57.06,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If a flame is extinguished, \Nit will not perceive the moment it was snuffed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:05:00.02,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Only the results of this world remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.28,0:05:05.20,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,In a world where time is erased, \Nevery move is rendered useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.57,0:05:09.37,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Only I alone can react to these moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.37,0:05:12.50,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I can see every single move you intend to make!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.50,0:05:15.87,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That is King Crimson's ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:34.56,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Th-This ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:37.77,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,No matter what kind of person you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:41.65,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...you'll experience ups and downs in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.65,0:05:44.86,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You win some, you lose some.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:53.70,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But if you witness the pitfalls open up right before your eyes, \Nergo the future, and choose to avoid them...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:56.62,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...you will never incur another loss for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:06:01.00,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You will experience unending pleasure.{Why yes, I did indeed see the whole explanation about how his analogies sound extremely sexual. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:04.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Don't you agree? Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:15.81,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Now that we've met in person, \NI know for certain we're related.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:21.31,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Without a doubt in my mind,\N I can sense that you are truly my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:24.36,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:30.53,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...if you were conscious at this very moment, \Nyou would sense it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:33.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:36.96,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I must avoid any pitfalls along my path!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:40.46,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The time has come to sever \Nthe blood tie that bonds us!{He literally just says "I will now sever this stream of blood", but that on its own is... pretty unclear. CR's translation actually makes it easier to understand his point, fancy that. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:42.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:48.97,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:55.39,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.85,0:06:59.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno's Gold Experience's ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:03.86,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,He planted the tortoise's cells \Nin the brooch and imbued it with life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:07.82,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...which gave birth to a tortoise with a Stand ability.{OH MY GOD THIS MAKES SO MUCH SENSE YOU GUYS seriously how are people complaining that KING CRIMSON's power is unclear? "It just works" seems FAR more fitting a description for Gold Experience. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:12.78,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,After our call was interrupted,\N he must have sensed danger and activated his ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:17.75,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,He always gives me courage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:22.13,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I didn't think I could move anymore, \Nbut... I'm not finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:24.67,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.42,0:07:28.46,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...go on for a bit longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:33.22,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,My mission has come to an end? \NBoss, you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.22,0:07:35.05,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's far from over!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.05,0:07:36.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As for Trish...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.97,0:07:39.73,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I order {\i1}myself{\i0} to protect her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:43.19,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,If he can read any attack I throw at him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:47.23,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...and I can't even perceive when he's dodged them...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:52.24,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...then his ability is more powerful than I could have imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:56.41,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Even so!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:08:03.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,His ability doesn't allow him to \Nread movements for very long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.21,0:08:06.17,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,It seems to have a short duration.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.50,0:08:09.59,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Perhaps five to ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.13,0:08:11.59,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:14.01,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,For now, I need to put distance between us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.59,0:08:17.76,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Enough distance so that the boss can't catch up to Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:22.02,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,My battered body, please move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:25.31,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno afforded me this chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:29.15,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I need to escape from the basement at the very least...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:32.95,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,So there's another traitor among you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:34.66,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,It must be the new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:40.50,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If my intel is accurate, \Nhis name is Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:44.87,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I suppose he must have joined my organization \Nwith the intent to betray me from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:49.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You seem to have thought you could escape merely by putting distance between us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:52.59,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...but escaping from the tortoise\N the instant before it was swept away was trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:56.59,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Your efforts appear to have been for naught, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.55,0:08:59.72,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,How can you still move?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.72,0:09:01.18,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Is it pure force of will?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:08.15,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,A moment's rest won't be enough for you to reach the first floor, \Nbut it should be plenty to make it to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:11.78,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,To start with, I'm going to eliminate Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:14.70,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Don't you dare move, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.70,0:09:18.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The chance Giorno afforded me wasn't for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:20.54,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If success here hinges on who reads the other's moves...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:22.33,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...then I've already won by reading yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.08,0:09:25.37,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I figured that before you were swept into the sewer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:28.29,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...you would probably use your ability to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.29,0:09:31.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now, Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.51,0:09:34.17,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,King Crimson!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:45.94,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Th-That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:49.77,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But within King Crimson's domain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:53.36,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...whether or not your actions were futile changes nothing!{He's saying that, since he has King Crimson's It Just Works power, Buccellati's actions were, and continue to be, a complete waste of everyone's time. -Starfish} {Wait what? If they were futile BEFORE he activated his ability, then why would he need to use his ability at all? I would expect that he's saying that his action becomes futile BECAUSE of King Crimson's world... Right? -Gyro}{I think this gets across what Lord Starfish way saying. -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.65,0:09:54.57,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.90,0:09:55.90,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:59.37,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,My attack wasn't aimed at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.37,0:10:01.03,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It was aimed at the pillar!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.03,0:10:03.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Zip up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:05.91,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:10.04,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As I thought... \NYour ability is invincible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:14.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But it's clear now that you can \Nonly read movements for a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:17.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You're not reading ahead of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:22.47,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Go ahead and try to read my future movements, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.93,0:10:27.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Try to figure out what I'm going to do in a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:29.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Try to look beyond time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:34.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you succeed, \Nyou'll have seen that I make it to the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:47.79,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati! Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:52.17,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This wound...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.59,0:10:54.00,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What happened in the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.55,0:10:57.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Where's the boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.34,0:11:01.97,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,He wouldn't have fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.97,0:11:03.76,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,He must be close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.64,0:11:11.77,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I don't know the full situation, \Nbut the boss will never let Buccellati go after this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:20.61,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:24.58,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.95,0:11:26.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.33,0:11:34.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,His pulse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:36.71,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I-It can't be! It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:40.34,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I replaced his damaged organs and stopped the bleeding!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:42.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, please breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:45.26,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That must be Giorno Giovanna.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.89,0:11:51.73,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,His unknown ability gave Buccellati \Nthe chance to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.73,0:11:52.81,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:55.61,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...neither of them will make it any farther!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.57,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:11:59.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm sure I made new organs!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:01.65,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,There's no reason his heart shouldn't be beating!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:03.78,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:06.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Call Abbacchio and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:07.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:12.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.42,0:12:15.38,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I just told you to call Abbacchio and the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:17.21,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.67,0:12:19.05,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Leave this church!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:20.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:22.01,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,B-Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:23.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:24.68,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You're alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:27.26,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hurry! \NHurry up and call the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:28.97,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,B-But we haven't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:32.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,There's no way we can uncover \Nthe boss's identity right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:35.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We need to get out of here, Giorno! \NWhile we still have distance from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:36.98,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,They're within my range!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.98,0:12:37.77,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.73,0:12:42.49,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll explain later! \NHurry up, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.78,0:12:46.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.33,0:12:52.91,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I see Giorno over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:56.71,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Hey, what the fuck, Giorno? \NGet over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:13:00.38,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,How are you gonna make up for \Ndefying orders and stepping foot on the island?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:01.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Buccellati's here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.97,0:13:04.34,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,H-How the hell did you get so beat up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:06.55,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Why are you coming back with Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.55,0:13:08.85,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:10.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.27,0:13:12.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Right now, we need to get out of here as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.23,0:13:15.02,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati, I commend you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:18.82,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I commend your excellent decision making skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:21.86,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Even though I possess the ability to eliminate time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:27.20,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...if I were to face six Stand users at once,\N I would be unable to avoid exposing myself to at least one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.91,0:13:33.54,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,For the time being...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.96,0:13:37.58,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...they've managed to escape my King Crimson.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:40.88,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But this is far from over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:42.51,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I will never...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:46.76,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...let them escape from Venice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.68,0:13:54.10,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now I understand not only how the boss has \Nreigned supreme, but why he's so feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:56.98,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We can't defeat the boss... Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:13:59.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Either we have to uncover his identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:01.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...or a weakness in his ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:05.40,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...assuming it even has one.
Comment: 0,0:14:08.03,0:14:08.07,Main,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:14.70,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:17.08,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What the hell's going on, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.08,0:14:18.50,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,We deserve an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:20.67,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:25.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right.\N I'll just come out and say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:32.01,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I won't go into detail since \Nwe're still in danger and don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:39.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The reason I brought Trish back here\N is because I just betrayed the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.31,0:14:42.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is where we'll part ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:48.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you choose to act alongside me, \Nyou, too, will be branded as traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:50.37,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.37,0:14:52.70,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-I don't think I heard you right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:55.08,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:58.75,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He said... he betrayed the boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:00.46,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Wh-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.38,0:15:04.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I probably shouldn't tell you more...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:07.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...since none of you are involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:10.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I think it would be best if you explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:13.60,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Some of them may choose to follow you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.14,0:15:16.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We need allies we can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:21.23,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Giorno, what the fuck is your deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.23,0:15:24.32,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,First you go inside the church without permission, and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:27.07,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.07,0:15:29.40,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What's wrong? \NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:30.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.41,0:15:34.87,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I feel a bit faint from the blood I've lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:37.50,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That shouldn't be possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.50,0:15:40.42,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,His blood should have been replenished\N after I replaced his organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:42.79,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Did I miss a wound?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.80,0:15:48.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I guess I've just used a lot of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.55,0:15:50.63,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Does he not feel pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:52.93,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I didn't see any blood come from his wound, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:53.93,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Am I seeing things?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:55.10,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:57.06,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You freaked me out for a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:15:58.47,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.47,0:16:00.35,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Buccellati, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:02.77,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Yeah, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.77,0:16:04.69,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,We want to know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:20.91,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The boss had us act as bodyguards\N so he could kill his daughter with his own two hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:24.67,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He's afraid someone could uncover his identity \Nthrough his blood relation with Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:26.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once I figured this out, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:29.63,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.63,0:16:33.97,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I couldn't come back here and feign ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.43,0:16:36.47,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's why I betrayed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.47,0:16:38.01,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,How could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.01,0:16:40.35,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Are you crazy, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.73,0:16:45.98,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,There's no way you're not aware of what happens \Nto traitors after they've made themselves known.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:49.03,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The boss has never let anyone get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.03,0:16:53.57,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Hell, Venice could already be \Nsurrounded by the boss's elite guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.57,0:16:57.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You're right. \NWhich is why I'm going to need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:16:59.83,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If any of you are willing to accompany me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.45,0:17:03.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...come down these stairs and get on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:08.09,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,However, this is not an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:10.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I don't expect any of you to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:13.59,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This was my decision to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:16.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,None of you are obligated to join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.51,0:17:19.97,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This may come off as arrogant, \Nbut I'm going to say it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I did this because I know I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.64,0:17:25.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I have no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:29.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,In spite of the state of the world we live in,\NI want to follow a path I know is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:32.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We just need to find his weakness...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.36,0:17:36.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Though I'm fleeing for now, \NI {\i1}will{\i0} defeat the boss, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:38.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I {\i1}will{\i0} find his weakness, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:18:03.77,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I understand your reasoning, \Nand I'll admit that you did the right thing, Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:06.31,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,...but I'm going to be blunt with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.10,0:18:10.52,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,It pains me to say it, \Nbut none of us will step on that boat with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.11,0:18:14.36,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,How could you let your \Nemotions get the better of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:17.78,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I may be in your debt,\N but that doesn't mean I'm going to accompany you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:20.66,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You've lost sight of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:24.00,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,No one can survive in this world on ideals alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:27.62,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We can't survive without the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:29.46,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Fugo's absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:32.84,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You've pretty much committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:37.43,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,No matter where in the world you run, \Nyou'll never find peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:41.14,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Besides, I've only pledged my loyalty to the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.64,0:18:44.39,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I didn't pledge a damn thing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:48.94,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,That said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:54.90,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I've never had a place where I belonged or could call home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:58.36,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The only time I've felt at ease...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:02.08,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,...is while I've been with you, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.45,0:19:05.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.96,0:19:09.92,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Y-You can't be serious, Abbacchio!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:12.75,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If somehow we figure out how to kill the boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:15.00,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...considering my skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:17.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...I'd say I'm next in the running to become a capo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.17,0:19:20.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Buccellati's a smart guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:23.93,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's the kind of guy who won't\N pick a fight he knows he can't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:26.72,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're gonna strike it rich for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.48,0:19:29.77,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Mista! Not you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:32.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Fugo, what are you gonna do? {I don't think it needs to be exact, just "are you coming or no?" -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:36.15,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You've all... l-lost your minds!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:37.99,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We're going to be completely isolated!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.99,0:19:40.11,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Wh-Where are you going to run to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:43.32,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Worse yet, \Nyou probably won't even make it out of Venice alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:46.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Narancia, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:50.92,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-I... d-don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.92,0:19:52.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Hey, Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.63,0:19:55.42,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.42,0:19:57.59,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Should I go with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:19:58.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Are you afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:01.68,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Yeah... I-I'm really scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.14,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,B-But just give me the order!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.14,0:20:07.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Your order will give me the courage to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:10.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Nothing can scare me as long as\N you order me to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:15.65,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is one thing I can't order you to do.\NYou need to decide for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.65,0:20:19.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You need to forge your own path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.61,0:20:24.87,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,B-But I don't know what to do!\N I seriously don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:26.83,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll warn you right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.58,0:20:29.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't come, Narancia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.87,0:20:31.54,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You aren't cut out for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.75,0:20:36.84,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:39.05,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You're all going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.05,0:20:43.09,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,There are things in this world that \Nyou just can't change, even if you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:46.85,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Our line of work has always been questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.85,0:20:49.85,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,How was this any different?{The exact phrasing here is "Isn't this a 50 steps, 100 steps problem?", which is in reference to a Japanese proverb originating in a story about some warriors running 50 steps away from a battlefield laughing at someone else who ran 100 steps, calling them cowardly, despite the fact that both of them ran away from the battlefield, so in short it's about the difference between two different things ultimately being negligible... All this to say that "How is this any different", while overly simplified and not making use of a proverb, is still true to the ultimate point Fugo is getting at. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.27,0:20:53.94,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,While I agree, I need to be true to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.07,0:20:58.11,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.11,0:21:01.65,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once this boat has left port, we'll all be traitors!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.95,0:21:08.79,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Why?\N You're all out of your minds!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.79,0:21:12.71,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,All this for a woman you just met \Nand have hardly spoken to!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:16.17,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You don't even know what kind of music she likes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:25.18,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Trish was abandoned by the people she trusted...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:30.81,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I was abandoned before, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.81,0:21:36.02,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I was abandoned by my dad \Nand my most trusted friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.73,0:21:40.48,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm pretty much just like her...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.06,0:21:40.48,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's none of our business what \Nthe boss does with his daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.07,0:21:45.20,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm pretty much just like Trish!
Comment: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:44.82,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,{\an8}All he had to do was turn a blind eye! \NI just don't understand! {I edited this, but I honestly think it's indistinct enough that it doesn't need to be subbed. Feel free to comment it back in though -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.62,0:21:49.74,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, hand me the tortoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.58,0:21:52.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's put Trish inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:53.29,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.08,0:21:57.25,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, please turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:22:00.59,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:06.13,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(680,1055)}I'm coming! I'm coming, too!\N I wanna go with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.59,0:22:09.55,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Don't order me not to come along!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.55,0:22:15.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Trish is me! And I'm Trish! \NThe wound on her arm is my wound!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.77,0:22:21.61,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Narancia... Not you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.03,0:22:24.82,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You fool... You're going to be killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.70,0:22:32.20,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I can't condone \Nsuch a foolish betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.79,0:22:35.41,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I won't be a righteous idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.17,0:22:44.01,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Took you long enough\N to make up your mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.01,0:22:47.13,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You better not hold this \Nagainst us later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.43,0:22:51.05,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Narancia, I highly respect your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:54.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I guess Fugo really isn't coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.77,0:22:57.77,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Well, that was his choice to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.81,0:23:02.69,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.69,0:23:06.36,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(800,1055)}I... I want to protect Trish!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.36,0:23:08.15,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(800,1055)}I'll defeat the boss with you!
